    yield svg.node();

}









This is a piece of digital art I created. It features bright colours, straight lines and some fun interactivity.


Try clicking the ‚ÄúBoogie!‚Äù button
You probably realize that my simple artwork is very similar to Piet Mondrian‚Äôs iconic Broadway Boogie Woogie. Broadway Boogie Woogie is considered one of Mondrian‚Äôs most emblematic paintings and whose aesthetic is instantly recognised all around the world. The original piece is housed today in New York‚Äôs Museum of Modern Art (MOMA).



Piet Mondrian‚Äôs original Broadway Boogie Woogie


Indeed, my amateur recreation is inspired by the original Mondrian, but not directly. In fact, it‚Äôs probably more accurate to say, my art piece is a derivative of a derivative.


